				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="人狼ドッチ (Werewolf Which)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>In &amp;#228;&amp;#186;&amp;#186;&amp;#231;&amp;#139;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#137;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#131;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#129;(lit. Werewolf Which, phonetically Jin-roh Docchi), a kind of a One Night Werewolf game, each player picks one of the two role cards for their hidden role for the game, and place the other face down on the table. This makes each player knows a role that should NOT in the town, in addition to their role, making deduction and bluffing more interesting.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As in One Night Werewolf, during the two discussion phases in a game, Civilians (non-Werewolf players) try to deduce who the Werewolves are, and Werewolf players try to hide/bluff their identity. There are special actions done before/between the discussion phases depending on the role, ranging from Seer or Cop to see the cards, or even DJ to exchange a player's role card to their unused card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then one and the only voting in the game is held to decide whom to expel from the town. Civilians win when a Werewolf gets most of the votes, otherwise Werewolves win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
